This paper combines techniques from deep learning, computer vision, and natural language processing to learn invariant representations that are disentangled from nuisance/sensitive variations. The paper focuses on the use of conditional variational autoencoders (VAE) with adversarial censoring, which are commonly used in the fields of machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
